NAME
    head - output the first part of a file

SYNOPSIS
    head [OPTION]... [FILE]...

DESCRIPTION
    Print the first part of each FILE to standard output. With no options,
    the first 10 lines are shown.

    This is the unmodified GNU coreutils head(1), ported to Horus and run as
    a ring-3 program from /bin/head over the fs_server.

OPTIONS
    -n [-]N    print the first N lines (or, with '-', all but the last N)
    -c [-]N    print the first N bytes (or, with '-', all but the last N)
    -q         never print file-name headers
    -v         always print file-name headers

    Run `head --help` for the full option list.

EXIT STATUS
    0 on success, non-zero on error.

SEE ALSO
    tail(1), cat(1), wc(1), hier(7)
